<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="307" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,356,885]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,356,381]" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons with a small black spot above antennal peduncle. Pronotal collar with a median and two pair of lateral facies, dark red or reddish. Pronotal disk with a median facie enlarged apically, dark red to black and two lateral black spots. Pronotal lateral margins concave. Humeral angles slightly infuscate but never with a black spot. Upper portion of vitta on propleura separated from lateral black spot of pronotal disk. Habitus in dorsal view 
<figureCitation box="[1364,1432,463,488]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[203,1394,1012,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[173,1429,991,1968]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Hyalopeplinus malayensis Carvalho in Carvalho &amp; Gross, 1979. 5. Habitus in dorsal view. 6. Endophallus. 7. Left paramere.8. Right paramere (specimen from Bengalor cited in the text)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169875/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
. Male genital structures 
<figureCitation box="[414,521,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1979,2002]" captionTargetBox="[203,1394,1012,1935]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[173,1429,991,1968]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Hyalopeplinus malayensis Carvalho in Carvalho &amp; Gross, 1979. 5. Habitus in dorsal view. 6. Endophallus. 7. Left paramere.8. Right paramere (specimen from Bengalor cited in the text)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1169875/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="307">Figs. 6–8</figureCitation>
. Measurements of Indian specimen table 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
